 20, 2000\n  | number_of_shows = 44\n}}\n\nThe '''Up in Smoke Tour''' was a [[West Coast hip hop]] [[Concert tour|tour]] in 2000 which was headlined by [[Dr. Dre]] & [[Snoop Dogg]], also featuring artists [[Ice Cube]], [[Eminem]], [[Proof (rapper)|Proof]], [[Nate Dogg]], [[Kurupt]], [[D12]], [[MC Ren]], [[Westside Connection]], [[Chilldrin of da Ghetto (album)|Chilldrin of da Ghetto]], [[Melvin \"Mel-Man\" Bradford|Mel-Man]], [[Tha Eastsidaz]], [[Doggy's Angels]], [[Devin The Dude]], [[Warren G]],  [[Crucial Conflict]], [[TQ (singer)|TQ]], [[Truth Hurts (singer)|Truth Hurts]], [[Xzibit]], [[The D.O.C.]], [[Hittman]],  Six-Two, and [[Ms. Toi]].\n\n== Background ==\n[[File:Up in Smoke Tour concert ticket.jpg|thumb|Ticket for the Up in Smoke Tour in Worcester, Massachusetts]]\nThe tour was originally called ''The Boyz in the Hood'' under the pretext of Dr. Dre's to-be-released collaborative album ''[[2001 (Dr. Dre album)|The Chronic 2000]]'' (later renamed).<ref>[http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1428281/19981214/dr_dre.jhtml Dr. Dre Almost Finished With \"The Chronic 2000\", Wants Snoop For First Single]. ''[[MTV]]'' (14 December 1998). Accessed 24 January 2008</ref> In September 1999, Snoop Dogg stated that he, [[Dr. Dre]], [[Eminem]], [[Xzibit]], [[Warren G]] and [[Nate Dogg]] would form the line-up.<ref>David Basham (15 September 1999). [http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1428266/19990915/dr_dre.jhtml Snoop Dogg Looks Forward To Chronic 2000 Tour With Dre, Eminem, Xzibit]. ''[[MTV]]''. Accessed 24 January 2008</ref> By April 2000, Ice Cube was on board as part of the tour, which was slated for a June 15 start in San Diego. [[MC Ren]], one time MC of [[N.W.A]], was expected to join the tour in order to have reunited version of N.W.A along with Dr. Dre, Ice Cube, and Snoop Dogg.<ref>[http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1428252/20000421/dr_dre.jhtml Dre, Eminem, Snoop, Cube Line Up Tour]. ''[[MTV]]'' (21 April 2000). Accessed 24 January 2008</ref> Come May, the tour was officially known as the ''Up In Smoke Tour'',<ref>David Basham (4 May 2000). [http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1428248/20000504/dr_dre.jhtml Dre, Snoop, Ice Cube, Eminem To Go \"Up In Smoke\"]. ''[[MTV]]''. Accessed 24 January 2008</ref> and Dr. Dre was promising fans \"It's gonna be incredible. We're gonna give everybody that's been buying our records a real show, something they've never seen before.\"<ref>[http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1428246/20000508/dr_dre.jhtml Dre, Eminem, Cube, Snoop Talk Tour]. ''[[MTV]]'' (8 May 2000). Accessed 24 January 2008</ref>\n\nBy June, the month which the tour began in, plans were finalised with [[Kurupt]] joining the tour. It was decided that he would start the opening set, which would be followed by Warren G and Xzibit, then Ice Cube would take the third spot whilst Eminem would take the fourth set. Dr. Dre would be the final set with collaborations including Snoop Dogg and the N.W.A reunion taking place during this segment. Ghostwriter and N.W.A affiliate [[The D.O.C.]] appeared on stage with Dre and Snoop Dogg on July 20, 2000 at [[The Centrum]] in [[Worcester, Massachusetts]], when they performed the intro to \"Let Me Ride\" and \"Still D.R.E.\".<ref>Syd Caesar. [http://geniusrap.com/hip-hop-dvds/the-up-in-smoke-tour.html The Up in Smoke Tour]. ''Rap Genius''. Accessed 15 February 2013</ref> Also, surprise guests were promised during various shows.<ref name=\"Tour Launch\">Elon Johnson (14 June 2000). [http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1428244/20000614/dr_dre.jhtml Dre & Em's \"Up In Smoke\" Tour Readies Launch]. ''[[MTV]]''. Accessed 24 January 2008</ref>\n\nIn October 2009, [[Aftermath Entertainment]] artist [[Bishop Lamont]] said to expect another Up in Smoke Tour when Dr. Dre's studio album, ''[[Detox (Dr. Dre album)|Detox]]'' was released. Expected to tour were: [[G-Unit]], [[Eminem]], [[Snoop Dogg]] and other Aftermath artists. However, with the cancellation of Detox, another Up in Smoke Tour is unconfirmed. In 2015 Dr. Dre hinted to a European tour similar to the Up in Smoke Tour, wanting to call it the Beats & Rhymes tour. Potential guests for the tour, according to Dr. Dre, would be Kendrick Lamar, Eminem and Snoop Dogg.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pitchfork.com/news/61597-dr-dre-says-he-wants-to-tour-europe-with-kendrick-lamar-eminem-snoop-dogg/|title=Dr. Dre Says He Wants to Tour Europe With Kendrick Lamar, Eminem, Snoop Dogg - Pitchfork|website=pitchfork.com}}</ref> A year later Snoop confirmed that the tour is still in the works.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.complex.com/music/2016/02/snoop-dogg-european-tour-update|title=Snoop Dogg Says That Epic Tour With Dr. Dre, Eminem and Kendrick Lamar Is Coming Together|website=Complex}}</ref>\n\n==Tour dates==\nThe tour's itinerary included the following cities:<ref name=\"Tour Launch\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! width=\"200\"| Date\n! width=\"200\"| City\n! width=\"150\"| Country\n! width=\"300\"| Venue\n|-\n| June 15, 2000 || [[Chula Vista, California|Chula Vista]] || rowspan=\"11\"|[[United States]] || [[Coors Amphitheatre (Chula Vista, California)|Coors Amphitheatre]]\n|-June 15, 2001 Herning, Denmark \u2013 Op i den her!\n| June 16, 2000 || rowspan=\"2\" | [[Anaheim, California|Anaheim]] || rowspan=\"2\" | [[Arrowhead Pond|Arrowhead Pond of Anaheim]]\n|-\n| June 18, 2000 \n|-\n| June 19, 2000 || [[San Jose, California|San Jose]] || [[San Jose Arena]]\n|-\n| June 21, 2000 || [[Sacramento, California|Sacramento]] || [[ARCO Arena]]\n|-\n| June 24, 2000 || [[Portland, Oregon|Portland]] || [[Rose Garden (arena)|Rose Garden]]\n|-\n| June 26, 2000 || [[Nampa, Idaho|Nampa]] || [[Idaho Center]]\n|-\n| June 30, 2000 || [[Indianapolis]] || [[Conseco Fieldhouse]]\n|-\n| July 1, 2000 || [[Columbus, Ohio|Columbus]] || [[Schottenstein Center|Value City Arena]]\n|-\n| July 2, 2000 || [[Cleveland]] || [[Gund Arena]]\n|-\n| July 3, 2000 || [[Pittsburgh]] || [[Mellon Arena]]\n|-\n| July 4, 2000 || [[Toronto]] || [[Canada]] || [[Molson Amphitheatre]]\n|-\n| July 6, 2000 || [[Detroit]] || rowspan=\"30\"|[[United States]] || [[Joe Louis Arena]]\n|-\n| July 7, 2000 || [[Auburn Hills, Michigan|Auburn Hills]] || [[The Palace of Auburn Hills]]\n|-\n| July 8, 2000 || [[Rosemont, Illinois|Rosemont]] || [[Allstate Arena]]\n|-\n| July 9, 2000 || [[Milwaukee]] || [[Bradley Center]]\n|-\n| July 10, 2000 || [[Minneapolis]] || [[Target Center]]\n|-\n| July 13, 2000 || [[Rochester, New York|Rochester]] || [[Blue Cross Arena]]\n|-\n| July 14, 2000 || [[Albany, New York|Albany]] || [[Pepsi Arena (Albany, New York)|Pepsi Arena]]\n|-\n| July 15, 2000 || [[East Rutherford, New Jersey|East Rutherford]] || [[Continental Airlines Arena]]\n|-\n| July 16, 2000 || [[Scranton, Pennsylvania|Scranton]] ||[[The Pavilion (Scranton, Pennsylvania)|Coors Light Amphitheatre]]\n|-\n| July 18, 2000 || [[Philadelphia]] || [[First Union Spectrum]]\n|-\n| July 19, 2000 || [[Uniondale, New York|Uniondale]] || [[Nassau Coliseum]]\n|-\n| July 20, 2000 || rowspan=\"2\"|[[Worcester, Massachusetts|Worcester]] || rowspan=\"2\"|[[DCU Center|Worcester's Centrum Centre]] \n|-\n| July 21, 2000\n|-\n| July 22, 2000 || [[Hartford, Connecticut|Hartford]] || [[Hartford Civic Center]]\n|-\n| July 25, 2000 || [[Buffalo, New York|Buffalo]] || [[HSBC Arena (Buffalo)|HSBC Arena]]\n|-\n| July 27, 2000 ||[[Washington, D.C.]]||[[Capital One Arena|MCI Center]]\n|-\n| July 28, 2000 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2000-07-28/features/0007280115_1_eminem-snoop-dogg-smoke-tour|title=Tour a show of rap unity|publisher=}}</ref> || [[Baltimore, Maryland|Baltimore]] || [[Baltimore Arena]]\n|-\n| July 29, 2000 || [[Charlotte, North Carolina|Charlotte]] || [[Charlotte Coliseum]]\n|-\n| August 1, 2000 || [[Sunrise, Florida|Sunrise]] || [[National Car Rental Center]]\n|-\n| August 2, 2000 || [[Tampa, Florida|Tampa]] || [[Ice Palace (Tampa arena)|Ice Palace]]\n|-\n| August 4, 2000 || [[Atlanta]] || [[Lakewood Amphitheatre]]\n|-\n| Aug